help.mtNamespace: The namespace is a category for the name/value pair tag. It may be used to distinguish groupings (e.g. crawling, processing) or to declare a true term namespace (e.g. dwc)

help.parentDataset: For use in declaring dataset relationships, such as the constituent parts of the Catalogue of Life
help.duplicateDataset: When a dataset is found to be a duplicate of another, then it should be updated. This will effectively trigger a de-index which is the same as a deletion. It may be that you ALSO need to set the parent dataset if this has been aggregated.
help.updateFrequency: The frequency with which changes and additions are made

help.instType: When changing this, verify all services are also updated for the installation, and every dataset served. Most likely you do not want to change this field, but rather create a new installation of the correct type, and migrate datasets. Use this with extreme caution
help.disabledCheckboxTip: Indicates that the installation is disabled and no metasync or crawling of associated datasets will occur
help.orgCommentsInfo: Comments allow administrators to leave context about communications with publishers etc.
help.orgMachineTagsInfo: Machine tags are intended for applications to store information about an entity. A machine tag is essentially a name/value pair, that is categorised in a namespace. The 3 parts may be used as the application sees fit.
